command.help:
Processes the schema and either create it directly on EntityManager Storage Connection or generate the SQL output.
<comment>Hint:</comment> If you have a database with tables that should not be managed by the ORM, you can use a DBAL functionality to filter the tables and sequences down on a global level:
$config->setFilterSchemaAssetsExpression($regexp);

Processes the schema and either drop the database schema of EntityManager Storage Connection or generate the SQL output. Beware that the complete database is dropped by this command, even tables that are not relevant to your metadata model.
<comment>Hint:</comment> If you have a database with tables that should not be managed by the ORM, you can use a DBAL functionality to filter the tables and sequences down on a global level:
$config->setFilterSchemaAssetsExpression($regexp);
